A Testimony☀️

My mother had been waiting and praying for years to receive money that she had been owed by the government.

While on lunch duty at school one day, a student had told us that their was stool in the urinal. The custodian at my school (a very hard working lady) was told about the incident. As I stood their watching her demeanor, she had a look on her face, a look of feeling completely defeated and tired (this was happening daily). The look on her face, left an indelible impression on me. 

In that moment the Lord told me to bless her. So, I did what the Lord asked me to do.

Afterschool I told my husband the story and how I felt I should do something for her. He encouraged me, so we went to Walgreens to buy a gift card.

The Lord told me the exact amount to give to her. 

The next morning, as I was arriving to school walking towards the building, she was walking out. PERFECT TIMING. I told her, “The Lord said this is for you and he loves you.” and gave her a hug.
She was touched and I felt so at peace knowing that I had just obeyed God. 

About 4 hours later my brother texts me, “Mom got good news, she’s getting paid soon. Love you.” In that moment I knew it was Him. It was all Him!! I couldn’t help but laugh

It was an INSTANT transaction. 

Yes, my mom had been praying for years. She never lost hope.
I had been praying too & what I did that day, I was not expecting anything in return.

There are things we can do that will cause Him to pay us back. 
Do something for someone who you know could never repay you and God will have to be the one to pay you.

The purpose of my post is not to gain anything in return or brag, but to give you hope. When you cant grab on to your faith, sometimes you have to fall back on your hope.

I pray that you will see His goodness. That you will do something for someone who can’t pay you back, not because you want something in return, but because you want to emulate His goodness and give that person hope. You are exactly what that person needs in that moment, don’t hold back. 

#faith #hope #believe #dontgiveup #blessings

Red bean is a popular Asian filling and it is one of my FAVORITES! 
Have you had before? 
I love it so much I decided to make my own without all the sugar and extra calories. 

14 oz Adzuki beans 
1c sweetener - I used 0cal Pyure organic granular sweetener 
Tsp of salt 

First go through the beans and discard any that are broken. 

Let the beans soak up to 8 hours OR for a quicker method. You can boil the beans. Once they begin to boil drain the beans and repeat for about 2 more times. 

Bring the beans to a boil. 
Cover the pot and reduce the heat to low. 
Allow them to sit for about an hour. 

You will know the beans are ready when they can easily mash between your fingers. 

Drain the beans and place them back into the pot with the heat on low. Mix in the sugar and salt until it dissolves 

Finally, place the beans on a flat surface to cool.

1/2 tsp salt

In a bowl mix the rice flour, salt, & sweetener well

Continue to add water and use your hand to knead the dough. 

The dough shouldn’t be sticky. Place it covered in a bowl for about 15 minutes.

Place the ball in water and dip into sesame seeds

Bringing back another cherished memory with a taste of my childhood with one of my favorite Korean dishes, Jajangmyeon. This is another popular dish that was only eaten on special occasions. The black bean sauce is savory and it doesn’t taste like beans 😉 

Save this recipe to try &  comment your favorite Korean dish, I’d love to know maybe I can make it next 😊

Meat of your choice (I used New York strip because it’s what we had) you can also use pork 
1 whole onion
1 potato 
1 zucchini 
1/2 large English cucumber 
Pepper & Ginger to season 
2 spoons soy bean paste 
Noodles - I used fresh round noodles 
1 spoon starch to thicken the sauce 
1tsp sweetener (I use stevia)
1tsp salt 

Slice up all your veggies and meat. 
Add the onions & add the meat and season with pepper and ginger 
Add potatoes 
When the meat is almost done cooking add a cup of water and 2 spoons of soybean paste. Mix it very well. 
Add the teaspoon of sweetener and salt. 
Now and the zucchini and cover. 

Prepare your noodles - when the water boils add your noodles to the pot. When the water begins to boil again add another cup of water and let it cook for about 6-8 mins. Drain and rinse. 

Check on your jajangmyeon and add the starch to thicken the sauce. Keep mixing it until sauce becomes somewhat thick. 

Pour the sauce over the noodles. Top with cucumber and sesame seeds. I also like to add Korean pickled radish it really brings all the flavors together 😍

Enjoy:)
